# ğŸ” Reverse a Number

## âœ… Code
```java
long long rev = 0;
int ld = 0;
while (n != 0) {
    ld = n % 10;           // Get last digit
    n = n / 10;            // Remove last digit
    rev = (rev * 10) + ld; // Build reversed number
}
return rev;
âœ… Explanation
rev: stores the reversed number.

ld: holds the last digit of the number in each iteration.

ğŸ”„ Steps:
Extract the last digit using % 10.

Divide n by 10 to remove the last digit.

Multiply rev by 10 to shift digits and add the new digit (ld).

Continue until n becomes 0.

ğŸ§® Example:
Input: 1234
Process:

Step 1: ld = 4 â†’ rev = 0Ã—10 + 4 = 4

Step 2: ld = 3 â†’ rev = 4Ã—10 + 3 = 43

Step 3: ld = 2 â†’ rev = 43Ã—10 + 2 = 432

Step 4: ld = 1 â†’ rev = 432Ã—10 + 1 = 4321

âœ… Output: 4321
â±ï¸ Time Complexity:
O(logâ‚â‚€ n) â†’ depends on number of digits in n.

âš ï¸ Edge Case:
If n = 0, the output is also 0.
